    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.54b-54c_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">15-2   Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">54b</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        412 Brookwood Dr. 
                        Champaign, Illinois 
                        2-28-59
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>My wife and I took your course "Epic America" in the summer of 1954 and we still talk about your philosophy and sincereness and greatness. Your philosophy has become our philosophy. We have your picture that was in the Alumnus magazine framed &amp; hanging in our living room &amp; we enjoyed the article that was in that issue very much.</p>
                
                <p>Last summer we visited and camped in the Black Hills of South Dakota. While we were there we talked to Benjamin Black Elk and his wife at Mount Rushmore.</p>
                
                <p>I didn't know him, so I mentioned your name, his eyes lighted up, and he explained his whole story and said what a great person you were, I agreed very much so. We all hope that you and Mrs. Neihardt are in the best of health and we want to thank you for the weiner roast &amp; the fun we had at your house that summer. Let us know if you have written any more books as we want to read them.</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.54b-54c_0002"/>
                    
                <fw type="curatorial">54c</fw>
                
                <p>I am sending your "<hi rend="underline">When the Tree Flowers<sic>Flowered</sic></hi>" to my brother &#8212; <address><addrLine>Norman Offineer</addrLine> <addrLine>514 Bank Street,</addrLine> <addrLine>Webster City, Iowa</addrLine></address> and we would like very much for you to autograph it for him, and send it to him. I have included the postage and only hope this will not put you to too much trouble. Thanks a million.</p>
                
                <p>I am teaching school in Urbana, Illinois now &amp; and my wife is <del/> working in the business office of Illinois Bell Telephone Co. I am enjoyin<del/><add>g</add> my hobby as a photographer very much and do this work during the summer.</p>
                
                <p>Thanks again and would appreciate very much hearing from you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Mr. &amp; Mrs. Kenneth Offineer</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
